description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE THIS POST IS FIXED TERM / SECONDMENT UNTIL 31 AUGUST 2021 TO COVER MATERNITY LEAVE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN APPLYING FOR THE SECONDMENT POSITION, YOU MUST OBTAIN PERMISSION FROM YOUR CURRENT LINE MANAGER PRIOR TO APPLYING FOR THIS POST. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an excellent opportunity for an experienced Human Resources Professional to join the Workforce &amp; Organisational Development Directorate to support the Rhondda Taff Ely Integrated Locality Group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Motivated and driven, the postholder will provide a full range of comprehensive and professional HR services. The role will work closely with others across the WOD functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will help drive forward the people agenda for the Integrated Locality Group across a variety of aspects including employee relations, recruitment, training and development and workforce planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for a CIPD qualified HR professional to develop within a challenging but supportive environment. The post will be based at Ponty Cottage Hospital with travel across the ILG locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 11th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tony Charles&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deputy Head of Workforce &amp; Organisational Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tony.Charles@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01443 443443 ext. 74009&lt;/p&gt;
